_:N0119da663fcc4116a393d6b86a3c134c <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Bas was appointed Director General for Immigration Enforcement at the Home Office in November 2023, following a long and varied career in public service.</p>\n\n<p>Born to Pakistani immigrants, he was raised in several locations across the UK and speaks a number of languages.</p>\n\n<p>Bas joined the Royal Navy in March 1988 as a helicopter engineer and served during Operation Desert Storm in 1991.</p>\n\n<p>He joined Avon and Somerset Police in November 1993 and held a number of operational leadership roles during his policing career, including detective chief inspector in Coventry, superintendent in Sandwell and chief superintendent in Solihull.</p>\n\n<p>He later joined the Metropolitan Police Service, where he served as Commander for Frontline Policing in London before becoming Deputy Assistant Commissioner for Professionalism from March 2021 to November 2023.</p>\n\n<p>Bas has studied criminology and has made academic contributions to the field.</p>\n\n<p>He has also served on the Board of Governors at Sandwell College.</p>\n\n<p>Outside of work, his interests include motorcycling, aviation, exercise and cooking.</p>\n" .
<https://www.gov.uk/> <http://schema.org/name> "Home" .
_:N17e75d59e84a454db3dbe5c7bf937d9b <http://schema.org/item> <https://www.gov.uk/> .
